notesStmt.note: Originally folio 213v contained a note of sale but is currently obliterated.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The Latter Prophets, accentuated and punctuated.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 20; written lines: 20; Uniform layout. Visible hard-point ruling. Hair side and flesh side of folios distinguishable. Jonah begins a new column and Amos opens a new leaf. The words and passages omitted by the original scribe supplied in the margin. Indications of the beginning and end of the Haftarot. Some masoretic notes. A vellum piece pasted at the back of the manuscript with a following note: נביאים אחרונים כתיבת יד רבינו תם.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Sefardi square script of the 12th or 13th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Latter Prophets. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Additional Ms. 4708.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Salomon da Costa, presented by him to the British Museum, 1759.
